      "role": "user",
      "content": "it felt way more intense than just a \"gut feeling\" though. like, it was literally a specific note that didn't belong in his tone. it was almost like a micro-tonal shift that happened right when he said \"on track.\" do u think there's actually a technical or biological reason why a lie would change the actual frequency of someone's voice? like, not just their tone, but the actual resonance?",
